# HPC (NHR@FAU) — vital commands

FAU Tier3 **Grundversorgung** (not Alex by default). Primary GPU cluster: **TinyGPU** (`tinyx.nhr.fau.de`). Docs: [doc.nhr.fau.de](https://doc.nhr.fau.de), local overview: `docs/HPC Info.pdf`.

## Account & paths

| Item | Value |
|------|--------|
| HPC user | `iwi5439h` |
| `$HOME` | `/home/hpc/iwi5/iwi5439h` (~50 GB) |
| `$WORK` | `/home/woody/iwi5/iwi5439h` (~500 GB) — **code, data, runs, conda** |
| Project on cluster | `$WORK/AcousticDrivenGeneration` |

Check quota: `shownicerquota.pl` or `quota -s`

## SSH (Windows `~/.ssh/config`)

- **Jump host:** `nhr-jump` → `csnhr.nhr.fau.de`, user `iwi5439h`, key `~/.ssh/id_rsa_hpc_fau`
- **TinyGPU:** `ssh tinyx` → `tinyx.nhr.fau.de`, `ProxyJump nhr-jump` (same user/key)
- **Woody (CPU batch):** `ssh woody` → `woody.nhr.fau.de`, same jump/key
- **No passwords** — keys only via [portal.hpc.fau.de](https://portal.hpc.fau.de); new keys may take **up to 2 h** to propagate
- Do **not** use `ProxyJump csnhr.nhr.fau.de` without a Host block (defaults to wrong user `dawoo`)

One-liner without alias:

```powershell
ssh -J iwi5439h@csnhr.nhr.fau.de iwi5439h@tinyx.nhr.fau.de
```

## TinyGPU Slurm

On `tinyx`, Slurm commands need the **`.tinygpu`** suffix: `salloc.tinygpu`, `sbatch.tinygpu`, `squeue.tinygpu`, `sinfo.tinygpu`.

| GPU | Interactive example |
|-----|---------------------|
| **A100** (40 GB) | `salloc.tinygpu --gres=gpu:a100:1 --partition=a100 --time=06:00:00` |
| **V100** (32 GB) | `salloc.tinygpu --gres=gpu:v100:1 --partition=v100 --time=06:00:00` |
| **RTX 3080** (10 GB) | `salloc.tinygpu --gres=gpu:rtx3080:1 --partition=rtx3080 --time=01:00:00` |

- **Frontend** `tinyx` = login only; **compute** nodes = `tg0xx` (check `hostname`, `nvidia-smi`)
- Long training → **`sbatch.tinygpu`**, not hours on frontend (CPU time limits)
- Queue: `squeue.tinygpu -u iwi5439h`; no exact queue position in Slurm

## Conda (one-time on cluster)

```bash
module load python
conda config --add pkgs_dirs $WORK/software/private/conda/pkgs
conda config --add envs_dirs $WORK/software/private/conda/envs
conda create -n acoustic python=3.11 -y
conda activate acoustic
```

**PyTorch on GPU node** — use **cu121**, not default pip 2.12 (driver mismatch → `cuda: False`):

```bash
export http_proxy=http://proxy.nhr.fau.de:80
export https_proxy=http://proxy.nhr.fau.de:80
pip install torch==2.5.1 torchvision==0.20.1 torchaudio==2.5.1 \
  --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu121
pip install -r requirements.txt
```

Verify: `python -c "import torch; print(torch.__version__, torch.cuda.is_available())"`

## Hugging Face (cluster often blocks Hub on compute nodes)

On **`tinyx`** (with proxy + token):

```bash
export http_proxy=http://proxy.nhr.fau.de:80
export https_proxy=http://proxy.nhr.fau.de:80
export HF_TOKEN=hf_...
export HF_HOME=$WORK/huggingface
huggingface-cli download google/flan-t5-small --local-dir $WORK/models/flan-t5-small
```

Train with local weights + offline:

```bash
export HF_HOME=$WORK/huggingface
export HF_HUB_OFFLINE=1
export TRANSFORMERS_OFFLINE=1
--model-name $WORK/models/flan-t5-small
```

## Project layout (naming)

| Artifact | Path pattern |
|----------|----------------|
| Tokenized data | `data/processed/<model-short>/<size>/tokenized/` |
| Training outputs | `runs/<model-short>/<size>/` |

Examples: `data/processed/flan-t5-small/100k/tokenized`, `runs/flan-t5-small/100k/`

`runs/` is gitignored. Match **`--tokenizer-model`** at prepare with **`--model-name`** at train.

## Prepare (CPU — `tinyx` or Woody `sbatch`)

```bash
cd $WORK/AcousticDrivenGeneration
conda activate acoustic
module load python
export http_proxy=http://proxy.nhr.fau.de:80
export https_proxy=http://proxy.nhr.fau.de:80

python -m main.prepare \
  --output-dir data/processed/flan-t5-small/100k \
  --train-size 100k \
  --tokenize \
  --tokenizer-model google/flan-t5-small
```

## Train (GPU — `salloc` or `sbatch.tinygpu`)

**Do not use `--fp16` on TinyGPU V100** — caused `grad_norm: nan` and bogus `loss: 0`. FP32 (no flag) is stable.

```bash
cd $WORK/AcousticDrivenGeneration
conda activate acoustic
module load python
export HF_HOME=$WORK/huggingface
export HF_HUB_OFFLINE=1
export TRANSFORMERS_OFFLINE=1
mkdir -p runs/flan-t5-small/100k

python -m main.train \
  --tokenized-dir data/processed/flan-t5-small/100k/tokenized \
  --output-dir runs/flan-t5-small/100k \
  --model-name $WORK/models/flan-t5-small \
  --num-train-epochs 3 \
  --per-device-train-batch-size 4 \
  --per-device-eval-batch-size 8 \
  --learning-rate 3e-4 \
  --weight-decay 0.01 \
  --warmup-ratio 0.1 \
  --logging-steps 100 \
  --eval-steps 5000 \
  --save-steps 5000 \
  --save-total-limit 2 \
  --seed 42 \
  --require-gpu
```

`--save-steps` must be a **positive multiple** of `--eval-steps`. Outputs: `runs/.../checkpoint-*`, `final_model/`, optional `test_eval.json`.

